Title : 2014 Italian Open – Men's Singles
Text : {{TennisEvents|2014|Italian Open|
|champ = {{flagicon|SRB}} [[Novak Djokovic]]
|runner = {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Rafael Nadal]]
|score = 4–6, 6–3, 6–3
}}

{{main|2014 Italian Open (tennis)}}

The '''2014 Italian Open – Men's Singles''' was the main men's event of the [[2014 Italian Open (tennis)|2014 Italian Open]] [[tennis]] tournament played in [[Rome]], Italy from 11 May through 18 May 2014.

[[Rafael Nadal]] was the two-time defending champion,<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.espn.co.uk/tennis/sport/story/208042.html|title= Nadal cruises to seventh Rome title|date=19 May 2013|work=ESPN|accessdate=23 May 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/tennis/22589283|title= Rafael Nadal beats Roger Federer in Italian Open final|date=19 May 2013|work=BBC Sport|accessdate=23 May 2013 }}</ref> but lost to [[Novak Djokovic]] in the final, 6–4, 3–6, 3–6.

==Seeds==
The top eight [[Glossary of tennis#S|seeds]] receive a [[Glossary of tennis#B|bye]] into the second round.

